A one sentence commit message is rarely enough when adding a feature.
PTAL.
friendly ping
Patchset looks good.  Needs a commit message.
as written, getLocationType calls isConnector internally.  Isnt' this duplicated?
yeah, I it is. I will remove it.
set internalError() here please.

I actually don't think that is too useful since we either check `isConnector` and we will never hit this error or we remove `isConnector` and any other interface will throw that error.

Any suggestion here?
isConnector is going away per the above comment.  As a general rule, if we get an enum value we don't expect, we should set internalError().

doesn't this mean that for any interface that is not part the if statements or a valid location type, then it will error out.

How about the cases where the interface just have extra interface for some other uses it will hit this case and fail.
Done
Why is this in the else? If we have a bunch of interfaces not in the else if above doesn't this get called more than once? Does this even need to be in the for loop?

it is in the else since we don't want to check the interfaces that matched the others which we know is not a location type.

It needs to be in the loop since we need to look thought all of the interfaces to determine the location type.
